# Cursor Rules for Noteably

## Project-Specific Rules

The following rules are tailored for the Noteably AI study material generator:

- **[project.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/project.mdc)** - Project overview, tech stack, architecture
- **[backend.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/backend.mdc)** - Django, DRF, Celery, API integrations
- **[frontend.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/frontend.mdc)** - Next.js, React, TypeScript, WebSocket
- **[database.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/database.mdc)** - Supabase, schema design, RLS policies

## Rule Structure

- **Required Frontmatter:**
  ```markdown
  ---
  description: Clear, one-line description of what the rule enforces
  globs: path/to/files/*.ext, other/path/**/*
  alwaysApply: boolean
  ---
  ```

- **Content Guidelines:**
  - Start with high-level overview
  - Use ✅ DO and ❌ DON'T examples
  - Show code examples with language tags
  - Reference actual patterns from PRD
  - Keep rules DRY by cross-referencing

## Key Patterns

- **Single-Page Flow**: All processing happens on one page with WebSocket streaming
- **Material Selection First**: User chooses outputs before processing starts
- **Tier-Based Features**: Check subscription before gated features (PDF export)
- **Real-Time Updates**: WebSocket events for transcription and generation progress
- **Simplified Providers**: AssemblyAI for transcription, Gemini for generation

